<%= partial :lang_select, id: id, lang: lang %>
<%= partial :privacy_js %>
<% lang = params["lang"] || lang %>

<h1>Pokémon Guessing Game</h1>
<div class="difficulty-select">
	<% if !session[:points] %>
		<h3>Enter username</h3>
		<form action="/<%= lang %>/game/start" method="post" id="difficulty">
			<select id="username-1" class="username-select" name="username-1" required>
				<% ('A'..'Z').each do | letter | %>
					<option value="<%= letter %>"><%= letter %></option>
				<% end %>
			</select>
			<select id="username-2" class="username-select" name="username-2" required>
				<% ('A'..'Z').each do | letter | %>
					<option value="<%= letter %>"><%= letter %></option>
				<% end %>
			</select>
			<select id="username-3" class="username-select" name="username-3" required>
				<% ('A'..'Z').each do | letter | %>
					<option value="<%= letter %>"><%= letter %></option>
				<% end %>
			</select>
			<div class="diff-hint">
				<p>Choose your username like in an old arcade game! You can choose between three different letters from A-Z. Or just leave it at the default and save your result as “AAA” in the leaderboard!</p>
			</div>
			<hr>
			<h3>Daily challenge</h3>
			<div class="diff-hint">
				<p>The daily challenge mode – this mode is particularly difficult with no hints available and a large amount of blur. You will be given a set of five Pokémon from Generation <%= GENS.keys.first.romanise %> to Generation <%= GENS.keys.last.romanise %> to guess from each day. Come back every day to try your luck!</p>
			</div>
			<div class="game-start-buttons">
				<button type="submit" class="full" name="daily" value="true">Start today’s challenge (<%= Date.today %>)</button>
			</div>
			<hr>

			<h3>Endless mode</h3>
			<select id="difficulty" name="diff" required>
				<option value="easy">🟢 Easy</option>
				<option value="medium">🟡 Medium</option>
				<option value="hard">🔴 Hard</option>
			</select>

			<select id="generation" name="gen" required>
				<option value="any" selected>*️⃣ Any generation</option>
				<option value="1">1️⃣ Gen I</option>
				<option value="2">2️⃣ Gen II</option>
				<option value="3">3️⃣ Gen III</option>
				<option value="4">4️⃣ Gen IV</option>
				<option value="5">5️⃣ Gen V</option>
				<option value="6">6️⃣ Gen VI</option>
				<option value="7">7️⃣ Gen VII</option>
				<option value="8">8️⃣ Gen VIII</option>
				<option value="9">9️⃣ Gen IX</option>
			</select>
			<div class="diff-hint">
				<p>Choose between three difficulty settings! The easiest will have the least amount of blur and the most number of hints whereas “Hard” will have a lot of blur and no hints at all! You can also choose to either have to guess the Pokémon of any generation (1-9) or you can choose to only guess Pokémon of a particular generation if you are more familiar with it.</p>
			</div>
			<hr>
			<button type="submit" class="full">Start Game</button>
			<div class="diff-hint">
				<p>Start the game immediately with the difficulty settings and the username you selected above!</p>
			</div>
			<hr>
			<a class="a-btn-2 full" href="/<%= lang %>/game/leaderboard/view">View leaderboard</a>
			<div class="diff-hint">
				<p>View the leaderboard and see the scores of other players – maybe you can even get to the top!</p>
			</div>
		</form>
	<% elsif session[:points] and !session[:challenge] %>
		<h3>Continue game</h3>
		<div class="diff-hint">
			<p>Clicking the “Continue” button will make your game continue where you left off. Your username and your difficulty settings will remain the same. To save your data in the leaderboard, to view your results or to see the leaderboard, scroll down. To reset the game, click the “Reset Game” button.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="game-start-buttons">
			<a class="a-btn-2 continue" href="/<%= lang %>/game/play">Continue</a>
			<a class="a-btn-2 continue" href="/<%= lang %>/game/reset">Reset Game</a>
		</div>
		<hr>
		<div class="game-start-buttons">
			<a class="a-btn-2" href="/<%= lang %>/game/results">View / download results</a>
			<a class="a-btn-2" href="/<%= lang %>/game/leaderboard/view">View leaderboard</a>
		</div>
		<% if !session[:saved_in_leaderboard] %>
			<%= partial :save_in_leaderboard %>
		<% else %>
			<form action="/game/leaderboard/save" method="post">
				<button type="submit">Override saved data in leaderboard</button>
			</form>
		<% end %>

		<hr>
		<div class="diff-hint">
			<p>Hint: If you want to try a new difficulty or generation or use a new username (so that your friend can play as well, for example), please use the “Reset Game” button.</p>
			<p><u>Resetting the game will reset all the counters</u>. If you want to continue where you left off and keep your score for this session, click the “Continue” button.</p>
		</div>
		<% elsif session[:points] and session[:challenge] %>
			<h3>Continue game</h3>
			<div class="diff-hint">
				<p>Clicking the “Continue” button will make your game continue where you left off. Your username and your difficulty settings will remain the same. To save your data in the leaderboard, to view your results or to see the leaderboard, scroll down. To reset the game, click the “Reset Game” button.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="game-start-buttons">
				<% unless session[:guesses] + session[:skips] == POKEMON_CHALLENGE_NUM %>
					<a class="a-btn-2 continue" href="/<%= lang %>/game/challenge/play">Continue</a>
				<% end %>
				<a class="a-btn-2 continue" href="/<%= lang %>/game/reset">Reset Game</a>
			</div>
			<hr>
			<div class="game-start-buttons">
				<a class="a-btn-2" href="/<%= lang %>/game/results">View / download results</a>
				<a class="a-btn-2" href="/<%= lang %>/game/leaderboard/view">View leaderboard</a>
			</div>
			<% if !session[:saved_in_leaderboard] %>
				<%= partial :save_in_leaderboard %>
			<% else %>
				<form action="/game/leaderboard/save" method="post">
					<button type="submit">Override saved data in leaderboard</button>
				</form>
			<% end %>

			<hr>
			<div class="diff-hint">
				<p>Hint: If you want to try a new difficulty or generation or use a new username (so that your friend can play as well, for example), please use the “Reset Game” button.</p>
				<p><u>Resetting the game will reset all the counters</u>. If you want to continue where you left off and keep your score for this session, click the “Continue” button.</p>
			</div>
	<% end %>
</div>
<h2>What is this?</h2>
<p class="block">A simple Pokémon guessing game where you will be presented with a blurred sprite of a Pokémon and will have to guess its name! The higher the difficulty, the higher the blur and the fewer hints you get – hard difficulty will not give you any hints at all! You will be able to decrease the blur by a certain degree as well as skip Pokémon you really cannot guess at all. You will also get a score counter that keeps track of how many correct guesses you have made and how many Pokémon you skipped! Try it out! If you reach a certain number of points, you can also unlock new themes for Theriodex that you can apply in the <a href="/settings">Settings</a>!</p>
